President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Tennessee and authorized Federal assistance to help with recovery efforts from a severe storm and straight-line winds that occurred on October 26, 2019. The Federal funding will be available to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, to help with emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities in the affected counties. The funding will also be available for hazard mitigation measures statewide. Manny J. Toro has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.